=head1 DESCRIPTION

Provides information about the directory on the Amazon EFS file system
that the access point exposes as the root directory to NFS clients
using the access point.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 CreationInfo => L<Paws::SecurityHub::AwsEfsAccessPointRootDirectoryCreationInfoDetails>

Specifies the POSIX IDs and permissions to apply to the access point's
root directory.


=head2 Path => Str

Specifies the path on the Amazon EFS file system to expose as the root
directory to NFS clients using the access point to access the EFS file
system. A path can have up to four subdirectories. If the specified
path does not exist, you are required to provide C<CreationInfo>.



